rotection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William de Pudsay was born about 1200, in England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Lady Pudsay. He died in 1268, at the age of 69."},"et":{"Abt 1200–1268":"umbes 1200–1268","1205–Female":"1205–Surnud","1250–1278":"1250–1278","1200–1268":"1200–1268","1205":"1205","1268":"1268","Abt 1200":"umbes 1200","1278":"1278","1200":"1200","1250":"1250","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1200–1268":"noin 1200–1268","1205–Female":"1205–Kuollut","1250–1278":"1250–1278","1200–1268":"1200–1268","1205":"1205","1268":"1268","Abt 1200":"noin 1200","1278":"1278","1200":"1200","1250":"1250","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1200–1268":"environ 1200–1268","1205–Female":"1205–Décédée","1250–1278":"1250–1278","1200–1268":"1200–1268","1205":"1205","1268":"1268","Abt 1200":"environ 1200","1278":"1278","1200":"1200","1250":"1250","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William de Pudsay est né environ 1200, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Lady Pudsay. Il est décédé en 1268, à l’âge de 69 ans."},"de":{"Abt 1200–1268":"um 1200–1268","1205–Female":"1205–Verstorben","1250–1278":"1250–1278","1200–1268":"1200–1268","1205":"1205","1268":"1268","Abt 1200":"um 1200","1278":"1278","1200":"1200","1250":"1250","England":"England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"William de Pudsay wurde um 1200 in England, United Kingdom geb